From a3fc77b10000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ETNA <etna@example.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix alterAnnotationsS to remove pops for removed pushes

Synthesised from upstream commit 5729c19b2a31 ("Fix alterAnnotationsS
removing only pushes, but not pops"). Reverse-applying this patch
reintroduces the bug where, for any annotation mapped to `Nothing` by
the user-supplied function, the corresponding push is dropped from the
output stream but the matching pop is *not* — so a subsequent SAnnPop
finds an empty stack and triggers `panicPeekedEmpty`. This affects
`unAnnotateS` (which is `alterAnnotationsS (const Nothing)`) on every
annotated layout.

---
 prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs b/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
index 0000000..0000000 100755
--- a/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
+++ b/prettyprinter/src/Prettyprinter/Internal.hs
@@ -1581,7 +1581,7 @@ alterAnnotationsS re = go []
         SText l t rest    -> SText l t (go stack rest)
         SLine l rest      -> SLine l (go stack rest)
         SAnnPush ann rest -> case re ann of
-            Nothing   -> go stack rest
+            Nothing   -> go (Remove:stack) rest
             Just ann' -> SAnnPush ann' (go (DontRemove:stack) rest)
         SAnnPop rest      -> case stack of
             []                -> panicPeekedEmpty
